{
  "text": "Since X gen is dense, we find an element x \u2208 \u2126 \u2229 X gen \u2229 \u00b5 \u22121 p (a). It follows from maximality of rk x \u00b5 p that \u00b5 \u22121 p \u00b5 p (x) \u2229 X gen is a closed submanifold of X gen . By Lemma 5.1 in [CITATION_1] , we obtain dim ker(\u00b5 p ) * ,x = dim(p \u00b7 x) \u22a5 . Hence, we conclude dim",
